Hello,

I've encounter a case where running a simple exploration on a function calling "[pthread_once](https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/procedures/posix/pthread.py#L82)" where the func argument (the function pthread_once call) points to a function containing the following assembly:
```
BX LR
```
(Branch Link Register)
Causes infinite loop to happen (LoopSeer does not stop it since it is not an actual assembly loop)

I've made a simple binary to replicate it, the C code:
```
#include <stdio.h> 
#include <errno.h>
#include <pthread.h>

int             once_counter=0;
pthread_once_t  once_control = PTHREAD_ONCE_INIT;

__attribute__((naked)) void immediate_return()
{
 asm("bx lr");
}

void pthread_once_bx_lr()
{
 pthread_once(&once_control, immediate_return);
}

void call_immediate()
{
 immediate_return();
}

int main(){}
```

Now If I run this simple exploration:
```
import angr
p = angr.Project(r"pthread_once", load_options={"auto_load_libs": False})
call_imediate = p.factory.call_state(addr=0x10534) # call_imediate
pthread_once_bx_lr = p.factory.call_state(addr=0x10510) # pthread_once_bx_lr

simgr_call_imediate = p.factory.simulation_manager(call_imediate)
simgr_pthread_once_bx_lr = p.factory.simulation_manager(pthread_once_bx_lr)

simgr_call_imediate.run()
simgr_pthread_once_bx_lr.run() # We get in infinite loop
```
The `immediate_return` function should have no problem running (since its only purpose is returning).
After some testing it seems the loop is getting stuck calling the [retsite](https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/procedures/posix/pthread.py#L94) function in pthread_once class - it keeps calling that function without calling the "run" function again.

Which is setup in [line 92](https://github.com/angr/angr/blob/master/angr/procedures/posix/pthread.py#L92) where we call it after calling the actual function (immediate_return)

