From `examples/platforms/efr32/radio.c`:

```
otError otPlatRadioTransmit(otInstance *aInstance, otRadioFrame *aFrame)
{
    RAIL_TxOptions_t txOption;
    ...
    txOption.waitForAck = (aFrame->mPsdu[0] & IEEE802154_ACK_REQUEST) ? true : false;
    ...
}
```

From Rail library rail_types.h:

```
typedef struct RAIL_TxOptions {
  /**
   * Configure if radio should wait for ack after transmit.  waitForAck is only
   * honored if Auto Ack is enabled and if Auto Ack Tx is not paused
   */
  bool waitForAck;
  ...
} RAIL_TxOptions_t;
```

Looks like we are not guaranteed the Rail library will wait for an acknowledgement on transmission if we have not setup auto ack and it's not explicitly done anywhere in the platform driver.

